&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;Are you an experienced guideline developer or systematic reviewer with experience in guideline development?&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h1&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;The Role:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;Reporting to the Senior Technical Adviser, the Technical Adviser leads the scoping team developing the scopes for guidelines and guideline updates. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;The role includes being responsible for methods and processes of scoping, scoping guidelines, managing the programme of work, and line management of 2 senior technical analysis and 1 technical analyst. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;You will also be responsible for leading on and contributing to methods and process for improving guideline development, supporting NICE connect as well as supporting quality assurance of guidelines.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h1&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;What you will bring to NICE:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;To be considered for this role, we are looking for:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt; &lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;Doctorate and further specialist training or equivalent level of knowledge acquired through experience and further training/development&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;Expert knowledge of the methods and practices of one or more of the following: guideline development, systematic reviewing, health services research, medical statistics, or health technology assessment&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;Ability to think and plan programme of work strategically, to adopt a flexible, agile and responsive approach to exercise sound judgement in the face of conflicting pressures&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;Experience of working with a wide range of stakeholders&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;Extensive knowledge of the principles of evidence-based health and social care&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;The post holder should be able to demonstrate the following:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt; &lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;Advanced theoretical and practical knowledge of different processes and methods for guideline development&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;Ability to establish effective working relationships and engage effectively with a wide range of stakeholders, both internally and externally&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;Experience of guideline development&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;Flexible and agile attitude to working environment and ability to work as part of a team&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;Thorough attention to detail and high standards of accuracy&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h1&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;Why NICE:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt; &lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;Here at NICE we are passionate and proud of the work we do and the impact we make.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;We can offer you a great place to work with good benefits, flexible working and a supportive, friendly and inclusive environment.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;We have an academic culture committed to producing high quality work and we take collective responsibility.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h1&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;The Department:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;The Centre for Guidelines (CfG) develops and updates clinical, public health and social care guidelines for the NHS and local authorities. These are recommendations on the appropriate prevention, treatment and care options for people, based on the best available evidence of effectiveness and cost effectiveness. Within the centre the methods and economics team provides quality assurance from a technical perspective throughout the development of a guideline, including, scoping, development and validation. The team also provides an analytical service to inform judgements about the need to update guidelines; the economists also contribute to guideline development. The team also lead on further development of methods in areas identified as priorities. The team also produces scopes for guidelines and guideline updates.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;For an informal discussion please contact Toni Tan, Senior Technical Adviser, on 0161 870 3105 (toni.tan@nice.org.uk).&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Closing date: 16th November&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;Interview date: 30th November&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
